          <!--<h1>Stratford Homes manufactures modular and prefab homes in Wisconsin, Iowa, Minnesota, Illinois and the surrounding areas.</h1>-->
          <h1>
           Get to know Stratford Homes.
          </h1>
          <h2 class="kcd2">
           We understand that the unique process of building a custom home should be a rewarding experience for every homeowner. Weve had the privilege of being part of over 12,000 new homes for families with a vision for energy efficiency, exceptional quality, structural strength, and customization capabilities. Stratford Homes has been providing custom-built homes using modular construction techniques since 1973. During this time, weve helped translate countless visions of that one perfect house into beautiful, new custom homes.
          </h2>
          <h2 class="kcd2">
           Whether your vision calls for one story living, a two-story design, a small cozy cottage, or an expansive chalet style home, Stratford Homes works hard to provide your home the way you want it with your lifestyle in mind. Youll appreciate the custom, high quality, name brand product offering and the modular construction advantages. Each of our homes is backed by a manufacturers one-year limited warranty. For added peace of mind, an optional 10-year insured limited warranty is also available.
          </h2>
          <h2 class="kcd2">
           At Stratford Homes, we always welcome the opportunity to help educate those needing clarification with the terms often used in the building industry such as pre-fab, manufactured or mobile homes, traditional stick-built, and modular homes. Feel free to reach out to us if you need a better understanding of the differences.
          </h2>
          <h2 class="kcd2">
           Partner with Stratford Homes and an independent Stratford Homes Builder, and it wont be long until you are living in your custom-built home with all the benefits of the modular construction process.
          </h2>
          <div class="fb-like" data-share="true" data-show-faces="true" data-width="320">
          </div>
